node.text:
Minimalism is not about having less — it’s the intentional search for happiness without distractions. ✨

Do you ever wonder why certain photographs linger with the viewer longer? Why sometimes the smallest point of interest makes the BIGGEST impression? Or how so much “nothing” can feel so compelling to a scene? 

Minimalist photography techniques add a powerful sense of storytelling to any genre — they evoke emotion, balance and drama to your frame. 

Join @cjonesphoto on Baffin Island for his NEW class Minimalist Photography to learn how to approach creating stronger images with a minimalist mindset. 

Class premieres on June 22 at 9AM pst — tap the link in bio to RSVP to the free stream. 

#minimalism #minimalistphotography #capturethewild #negativespace #createeveryday #outdoorphotography #minimalistphoto #creativelive

And no this isn't some kind of cruel April Fool's joke 😂

In addition to our thousands of online classes, we at CreativeLive want to help our worldwide community stay even more connected and inspired during this time of need. SO...we’re excited to announce CreativeLive TV – our free, 24/7 variety show, live-streamed from the living rooms, studios, and kitchen tables of our worldwide creative community. You can expect musical performances, crafting, live Q&As, cooking, spoken word, drawing, and more - featuring many of our favorite personalities - all in a safe, virtual space full of joy, shared experiences, and connection via live, interactive chat.

Today we're kicking off the LIVE stream with a lineup up of heavy hitters from a performance from @joshuaromancello to restaurant and small business advice courtesy of @canlisrestaurant to tips on how to stay social connected while social distancing from @vvanedwards. Tap the link in bio to tune in LIVE.

node.text:
Make your creative ideas a reality with @brookeshaden and Microsoft @Surface.

The multifaceted Brooke Shaden, explores the juxtaposition of the dark and light in people through her captivating work. As a self-portrait artist, she photographs herself and becomes the characters of dreams inspired by a childhood of intense imagination and fear. Being the creator and the actor, Brooke controls her darkness and confronts those fears.

After studying film in college, she realized her love of storytelling was universal. She started photography then in 2008, excited to create in solitude and take on character roles herself. Brooke works from a place of theme, often gravitating toward death and rebirth or beauty and decay

While her images come from a personal place of exploration, the goal in creating is not only to satisfy herself; her greatest wish is to show others a part of themselves. Art is a mirror for the creator and the observer.

Catch some of her NEW, FREE classes for FREE thanks to our friends at powered by our friends @Microsoft @Surface.
